The paper deals with privacy and surveillance in networked systems, which suggests categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The use of synthetic and real-world datasets, as well as the mention of laws and regulations, also suggests categories such as cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DB (Databases).
